<p><span id="internal-source-marker_0.30517161288298666">In Peru's Ca√±ete River valley, CIP entomologists designed an IPM package to help growers protect their crops against the leafminer fly, which had become a major problem after massive use of insecticides exterminated its natural enemies.</span><br /><span></span><br /><span>The IPM program included traps to lure and kill adult flies and reintroduction of parasitic wasps. Participating growers were able to reduce spraying from 12 times per season to only 1 or 2 carefully timed applications of insect growth regulators.</span></p>